HEADWORD: Paulician
<hw>Pau"li*cian</hw> <pr>(p⟦add⟧"l⟦icr⟧*sh⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Etymol. uncertain.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a
sect of Christian dualists originating in <country>Armenia</country> in
the seventh century. They rejected the Old Testament and the part of the
New.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

